From the Cheap Seats

On a creative WBD concession: =E2=80=9COf course, the NBA improved the WNBA=
=E2=80=99s deal well beyond what WNBA management even dreamed about. But st=
ill, it=E2=80=99s paltry. Risky, too, as no one knows if the surge in WNBA =
popularity is sustainable. It may be too late, but why wouldn=E2=80=99t the=
 NBA offer WBD a new special package of WNBA games? It could be positioned =
as the opportunity for WBD to literally make the WNBA into a powerhouse, ju=
st like Turner did with the NBA in the =E2=80=9990s. We forget how David St=
ern and Robert Wussler took a poor product and turned it into a money machi=
ne. Given the low dollar figures for WNBA, WBD gets a bargain and saves fac=
e. And, if they succeed, there is a whole new product to sell in just four =
years.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94A cable executive

On Zaz=E2=80=99s negotiating tactics: =E2=80=9CZaz=E2=80=99s NBA failure is=
 like
scoring an own goal during stoppage time with 10 seconds left to lose the W=
orld Cup=E2=80=A6 only worse.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94Another cable executive

On WBD=E2=80=99s NBA lawsuit: =E2=80=9CAt this point, it seems to be just a=
n effort to squeeze out a cash settlement. Without the benefit of reading t=
he contract, there=E2=80=99s little chance a court would ever order any sor=
t of injunction. So then it=E2=80=99s just about damages=E2=80=94and how ar=
e they going to argue any damage when Zaslav said it=E2=80=99s a money lose=
r?=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94A satisfied Varsity subscriber

On Puck=E2=80=99s NBA reporting: =E2=80=9CThursday night Ourand ticktock: s=
hot. Friday night Byers on the WBD Edelman clown show: chaser. Puck might a=
s well be called the =E2=80=98Zaz Cinematic Universe=E2=80=99 at this point=
! As a subscriber, I=E2=80=99m loving the coverage.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94A spo=
rts content executive

On my appearance on Lauren Sherman=E2=80=99s Fashion People pod: =E2=80=9CA=
re we in a safe space where I can admit that the acronym LVMH has
never before landed in my brain?=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94A former ESPNer

See you Thursday,
John

