e NBA</i> to Amazon, NBC, or even ESPN. But WBD sources tell me that the ch=
ances of that happening are so small that it=E2=80=99s not worth discussing=
=2E Plus, there are questions about whe=
ther those networks even want that sho=
w. Sure they covet some of the talent, like <b>Sir Charles</b> and <b>Shaq<=
/b>. But they have expressed little interest in bringing over the whole pro=
duction.<br/><br/>Which brings us to Barkley, who <u><a href=3D"https://ema=
il.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dSQVF0TzAzcEZ3TF=
VvdXRvamphcz0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubnl0aW1lcy5jb20vYXRobGV0aWMvNTY2M=
Dg1Ny8yMDI0LzA3LzI2L2NoYXJsZXMtYmFya2xleS10bnQtY29udHJhY3QtZnJlZS1hZ2VudC1l=
c3BuLW5iYy1hbWF6b24vP3V0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1UaGUrVmFyc2l0eSstK1NVQlNDUklCRVJTKyU=
yODclMkYyOSUyRjI0JTI5XHUwMDI2dXRtX2NvbnRlbnQ9VGhlK1ZhcnNpdHkrLStTVUJTQ1JJQk=
VSUyslMjg2JTJGNiUyRjI0JTI5XHUwMDI2dXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbF9hY3Rpb25cdTAwMjZ1d=
